#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:233
msgid "sample.appendix.content"
msgstr "# Technical Reference\n\n## File Structure\n\nActive EPUBs follow this enhanced structure:\n\n```\nyour-book.epub\n├── mimetype\n├── META-INF/\n│   ├── container.xml\n│   └── com.apple.ibooks.display-options.xml\n├── OEBPS/\n│   ├── content.opf          # Package document\n│   ├── toc.xhtml           # Table of contents\n│   ├── Text/               # Chapter content\n│   ├── Images/             # Graphics and media\n│   └── Styles/             # CSS stylesheets\n└── SOURCE/\n    ├── text/               # Plain text sources\n    ├── scripts/            # Transform processors\n    └── settings.json       # Editor configuration\n```\n\n## Transform Pipeline\n\nThe conversion process works as follows:\n1. **Source Text**: Written in markdown-like plain text\n2. **Text Transform**: Converts to basic HTML structure\n3. **DOM Transform**: Adds navigation IDs and EPUB-specific elements\n4. **XHTML Output**: Valid EPUB content ready for reading\n\n## Extending the Editor\n\nCustomize functionality by modifying:\n- **Transform Scripts**: Add new formatting rules\n- **CSS Styles**: Change visual appearance\n- **Settings**: Configure editor behavior\n\nThe modular design ensures your customizations remain intact when sharing or updating the EPUB file.\n\n*Build better books with Active EPUB technology.*"

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:232
msgid "sample.appendix.title"
msgstr "Technical Reference"

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:160
#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:89
msgid "sample.author.name"
msgstr "EDITME Editorial Team"

