msgid "sample.book.description"
msgstr "A comprehensive guide to creating and editing EPUB files with Active EPUB technology. Learn how to build interactive digital books with embedded editors and plain text workflows."

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:157
#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:87
msgid "sample.book.title"
msgstr "Introduction to EPUB"

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:219
msgid "sample.chapter1.content"
msgstr "# Getting Started with Active EPUB\n\nWelcome to the world of **Active EPUB** - a revolutionary approach to digital publishing that puts the power of content creation directly into your EPUB files.\n\n## What Makes Active EPUB Special?\n\nUnlike traditional EPUB files that are static once created, Active EPUB files contain their own editing environment. This means:\n\n- **Self-contained editing**: No need for external software\n- **Plain text workflow**: Write in simple, readable format\n- **Automatic transformation**: Your text becomes beautifully formatted EPUB content\n- **Embedded editor**: The editing tools travel with your book\n\n## Your First Steps\n\n1. **Explore the interface**: Navigate through the different sections using the sidebar\n2. **Edit metadata**: Customize your book's title, author, and description\n3. **Browse the manifest**: See all the files that make up your EPUB\n4. **Preview content**: Watch your changes appear in real-time\n\n## The Plain Text Advantage\n\nActive EPUB uses a simple text format that's easy to read and edit:\n\n```\n# This becomes a heading\n**This text is bold**\n*This text is italic*\n\nParagraphs are separated by blank lines.\n```\n\nThis approach keeps your content portable and future-proof while still creating professional-looking books.\n\n*Ready to dive deeper? Continue to the next chapter to learn about advanced features.*"

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:218
msgid "sample.chapter1.title"
msgstr "Getting Started"

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:226
msgid "sample.chapter2.content"
msgstr "# Advanced Features and Customization\n\nNow that you've mastered the basics, let's explore the powerful features that make Active EPUB truly special.\n\n## Transform Scripts\n\nOne of the most powerful features of Active EPUB is the ability to customize how your plain text is converted to EPUB content through **transform scripts**.\n\n### Text Transformations\n\nThe text transformation pipeline works in two stages:\n\n1. **Text Transform**: Converts your plain text to basic HTML\n2. **DOM Transform**: Adds EPUB-specific elements and navigation\n\nYou can customize both stages by modifying the transform scripts in your book's SOURCE folder.\n\n### Custom Formatting\n\nCreate your own formatting rules:\n\n```javascript\n// Example: Convert [[note]] to footnote\ntext = text.replace(/\\[\\[(.+?)\\]\\]/g, '<footnote>$1</footnote>');\n```\n\n## Workspace Management\n\nActive EPUB includes a complete workspace system:\n\n- **Multiple projects**: Switch between different books easily\n- **Auto-save**: Your work is saved automatically\n- **Version control**: Track changes to your content\n- **Export options**: Generate standard EPUB files when ready\n\n## Collaboration Features\n\nShare your Active EPUB files with others:\n\n- **Self-contained**: Recipients can edit without installing software\n- **Plain text sources**: Easy to version control with Git\n- **Portable**: Works on any modern device with a web browser\n\n## Performance Optimization\n\nActive EPUB is built for performance:\n\n- **OPFS storage**: Lightning-fast file operations\n- **Lazy loading**: Only loads content when needed\n- **Compression**: Efficient storage of resources\n\n*In the next section, we'll explore the technical details of how Active EPUB works under the hood.*"

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:225
msgid "sample.chapter2.title"
msgstr "Advanced Features"

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:212
msgid "sample.prologue.content"
msgstr "This document demonstrates the power of **Active EPUB** technology - a revolutionary approach to digital publishing that embeds a complete editing environment directly within EPUB files.\n\n## What You're Looking At\n\nYou're not just reading a book - you're experiencing an **Active EPUB**. This means:\n\n- ✨ **Self-editing capability**: This EPUB file contains its own editor\n- 📝 **Plain text sources**: Content is stored in readable, editable format\n- 🔄 **Live transformation**: Text automatically becomes beautiful EPUB content\n- 📱 **Universal compatibility**: Works on any device with a modern web browser\n\n## How It Works\n\nActive EPUB extends the standard EPUB format by including:\n\n1. **SOURCE folder**: Contains your plain text content and editing scripts\n2. **EDITME.html**: The embedded editor application\n3. **Transform pipeline**: Converts your text to valid EPUB content\n4. **Workspace system**: Manages multiple projects and file storage\n\n## The Plain Text Advantage\n\nUnlike traditional word processors, Active EPUB uses simple, readable text:\n\n```\n# This becomes a chapter heading\n**Bold text** and *italic text*\n\nParagraphs are separated by blank lines.\n```\n\nThis approach ensures your content is:\n- **Future-proof**: Plain text never becomes obsolete\n- **Version-controllable**: Easy to track changes with Git\n- **Portable**: Works across all platforms and devices\n- **Readable**: No complex formatting codes\n\n## Ready to Explore?\n\nUse the sidebar to navigate through different sections:\n- **Metadata**: Edit book information\n- **Manifest**: Browse all book files\n- **Content**: Edit and preview chapters\n- **Settings**: Customize your editing experience\n\n*Welcome to the future of digital publishing!*"

#: /Users/stewart/Projects/editme-svelte/src/lib/content/sample-content-generator.ts:211
msgid "sample.prologue.title"
msgstr "Welcome to Active EPUB"

